<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,791]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,513,539]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Koehler" box="[325,491,513,539]" firstAuthor="Koehler" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 317" refId="ref185837" refString="Koehler, R. (1909) Echinodermes provenant des campagnes du yacht Princesse-Alice (Asteries, Ophiures, Echinides et Crinoides). Resultats des campagnes scientifiques accomplies sur son yacht par Albert Ier Prince Souverain de Monaco, 34, 1 - 317." type="journal article" year="1909">Koehler (1909</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Koehler" box="[503,573,513,539]" firstAuthor="Koehler" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 173" refId="ref185883" refString="Koehler, R. (1914 a) A Contribution to the Study of Ophiurans of the United States National Museum. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 84, 1 - 173. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 03629236.84.1" type="journal article" year="1914" yearSuffix="a">1914a</bibRefCitation>
) remarked on the variability present in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lyman" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[1021,1282,513,539]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Amphiophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="convexa">
<emphasis box="[1021,1282,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Amphiophiura convexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyman, 1860" authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1860" baseAuthorityName="Lyman" baseAuthorityYear="1878" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioglypha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="convexa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Ophioglypha convexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), which in certain aspects of its morphology resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thomson, 1877)" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1877" baseAuthorityName="Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[927,1245,549,575]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Amphiophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis box="[927,944,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[959,1038,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">bullata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Thomson" box="[1054,1237,549,575]" firstAuthor="Thomson" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refId="ref202467" refString="Thomson, W. (1877) The voyage of the &quot; Challenger &quot;: the Atlantic. Vol. 1. Macmillan, London, 424 pp." type="book" year="1877">Thomson, 1877</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Paterson" box="[1257,1436,548,575]" firstAuthor="Paterson" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 162" refId="ref195005" refString="Paterson, G. L. J. (1985) The deep-sea Ophiuroidea of the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Zoology Series, 49 (1), 1 - 162." type="journal article" year="1985">Paterson (1985)</bibRefCitation>
based on the variability of the dorsal plating of the disc, assumed 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyman, 1860" authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1860" baseAuthorityName="Lyman" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[887,1010,585,611]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioglypha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="convexa">
<emphasis box="[887,904,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[918,1010,586,611]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">convexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[1256,1366,585,611]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Amphiophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis box="[1256,1273,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1287,1366,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">bullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Martynov &amp; Litvinova" firstAuthor="Martynov" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" refId="ref189845" refString="Martynov, A. V. &amp; Litvinova, N. M. (2008) Deep-water Ophiuroidea of the northern Atlantic with descriptions of three new species and taxonomic remarks on certain genera and species. Marine Biology Research, 4, 76 - 11. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 17451000701840066" type="book" year="2008">Martynov &amp; Litvinova (2008)</bibRefCitation>
disagreed and maintained the specific status, a view followed herein.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[151,1437,152,791]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<bibRefCitation author="Jesus &amp; Abreu" box="[199,446,657,683]" firstAuthor="Jesus" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="59 - 69" refId="ref184817" refString="Jesus, D. &amp; Abreu, A. D. (1998) Contribution to the knowledge of the soft bottom echinoderms of Madeira Island. Boletim do Museu Municipal do Funchal (Historia Natural), 50 (286), 59 - 69., 4 figs." type="book chapter" year="1998">Jesus &amp; Abreu (1998)</bibRefCitation>
reported an ‘ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[598,883,657,683]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Amphiophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="bullata">
<emphasis box="[598,760,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Amphiophiura</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[804,983,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis box="[804,883,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">bullata</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Lyman, 1860" authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1860" baseAuthorityName="Lyman" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[891,983,658,683]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioglypha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="convexa">
<emphasis box="[891,983,658,683]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">convexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ from 
<collectingRegion box="[1060,1153,657,683]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Madeira</collectingRegion>
shallow waters, between 20 and 
<specimenCount box="[235,313,693,719]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="generic">
<quantity box="[235,309,693,719]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" unit="m" value="100.0">100 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
In the North Atlantic, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matsumoto" authorityYear="1915" box="[684,846,693,719]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Amphiophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[684,846,693,719]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Amphiophiura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes strictly deep-water species that tend to live well below 
<quantity box="[281,373,729,755]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" unit="m" value="1.0">1,000 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Paterson" box="[387,551,728,755]" firstAuthor="Paterson" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="1 - 162" refId="ref195005" refString="Paterson, G. L. J. (1985) The deep-sea Ophiuroidea of the North Atlantic Ocean. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Zoology Series, 49 (1), 1 - 162." type="journal article" year="1985">Paterson 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Smirnov" box="[562,726,729,755]" firstAuthor="Smirnov" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="192 - 209" refId="ref200807" refString="Smirnov, I. S., Piepenburg, D., Ahearn, C. &amp; Juterzenka, K. V. (2014) Deep-sea fauna of European seas: An annotated species check-list of benthic invertebrates living deeper than 2000 m in the seas bordering Europe. Ophiuroidea. Invertebrate Zoology, 11 (1), 192 - 209. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / invertzool. 11.1.18" type="journal article" year="2014">Smirnov 2014</bibRefCitation>
). In light of this, we doubt that the material reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jesus &amp; Abreu" firstAuthor="Jesus" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" pagination="59 - 69" refId="ref184817" refString="Jesus, D. &amp; Abreu, A. D. (1998) Contribution to the knowledge of the soft bottom echinoderms of Madeira Island. Boletim do Museu Municipal do Funchal (Historia Natural), 50 (286), 59 - 69., 4 figs." type="book chapter" year="1998">Jesus &amp; Abreu (1998)</bibRefCitation>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName authority="Lyman, 1860" authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1860" baseAuthorityName="Lyman" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[433,556,765,791]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophioglypha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="convexa">
<emphasis box="[433,556,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">A. convexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or even the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matsumoto" authorityYear="1915" box="[766,928,765,791]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Amphiophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[766,928,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Amphiophiura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
